<!-- --8<-- [start:install] -->
You can install the GitHub handler by specifying it as a dependency:

```toml title="pyproject.toml"
# PEP 621 dependencies declaration
# adapt to your dependencies manager
[project]
dependencies = [
    "mkdocstrings-github",
]
```

after which the generated documentation can be inserted in the markdown page with:

```md
::: <path-to-action-or-workflow>
    handler: github
```

<!-- --8<-- [end:install] -->

<!-- --8<-- [start:footer] -->

## Features

- üìù **Automatic Example Signature**: Displays an example call signature alongside the description. The version shown can be the latest release, latest major, current reference, or any custom string.
- ‚ú® **Enhanced Markdown Descriptions**: All description elements are parsed using a markdown parser, enabling comprehensive formatting and rich documentation capabilities.
- üß© **Individual Parameter Hyperlinks**: Each action or workflow parameter‚Äîincluding inputs, outputs, and secrets‚Äîreceives a unique HTML id, facilitating direct linking to specific parameter documentation.
- üîí **Automated Permission Aggregation**: For reusable workflows, if permissions are specified at the job level rather than the workflow level, the required final permissions are automatically determined and displayed in the signature.
- üîó **Parameter cross-linking**: Link to other parameters of the action or workflow via a simple Markdown syntax.
- üßë‚Äçü§ù‚Äçüßë **Parameter grouping**: Organize related inputs, outputs, and secrets into visual groups using inline YAML comments for clearer documentation structure.

